His letter addressed to Atticus (111 19) on the 16th of September is a living testimony of the impatience and deep despondency which had laid hold on him. When his enemy Piso entered on his province of Macedonia, Thessalonica was no longer a sase abiding-place for Cicero. He accordingly abandoned this asylum and arrived at Dyrrhachium, which was a free town, on the 16th of November.
